The paper deals with algorithms for sequence comparison, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The paper presents an alignment-free technique based on minimal absent words, which is a combinatorial concept. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer science that deal with algorithms, combinatorics, and data structures. Specifically, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are all possible sub-categories that could be relevant to this paper. Among these, cs.DS and cs.CC are the most likely sub-categories, as the paper deals with algorithmic techniques for sequence comparison.
